WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Accumulus' is a Workbench game where you click on various types
of tiles. As tiles are clicked on, they disappear and tiles above
them fall down in the vacated spaces. The goal is to get tiles to
fall so no tiles of the same type are placed next to each other.

  When tiles fall down and none of them are next to tiles of the
same type, you get points according to the number of fallen tiles
that have neighbouring tiles (1 tile = 1 point, 2 tiles = 2
points, 3 tiles = 4 points, and so on... up to 256 points)...

  On the other hand, if 2 or more fallen tiles of the same type
are next to each other, these tiles will 'flash' and then TWO more
tiles will appear on the game board.

  Be careful that the game board does not fill up completely, as
that would end the game.
 
  Have fun!

